  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (55dd5de 2023-11-24T00:16:54.792480251Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge doc\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI document several contracts with NatSpec.\r\nIn some of these comments, more specifically in `@notice` tags, I like to add unordered lists. The problem is that in the HTML pages compiled by `forge doc`, everything that comes after these unordered lists is also part of the unordered list, even after empty lines.\r\n\r\nHere is an example Solidity contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 (see LICENSE)\r\n\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.8;\r\n\r\n/// @notice Here is a list of fruits:\r\n///\r\n/// * bananas\r\n/// * apples\r\n/// * pears\r\n///\r\n/// And here is a list of shapes:\r\n///\r\n/// * circle\r\n/// * square\r\n/// * triangle\r\n///\r\ncontract Foo {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere is the relevant part of the HTML output:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<p>Here is a list of fruits:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>bananas</li>\r\n<li>apples</li>\r\n<li>pears\r\nAnd here is a list of shapes:</li>\r\n<li>circle</li>\r\n<li>square</li>\r\n<li>triangle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I expected was something like this instead:\r\n\r\nHere is the relevant part of the HTML output:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<p>Here is a list of fruits:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>bananas</li>\r\n<li>apples</li>\r\n<li>pears</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>And here is a list of shapes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>circle</li>\r\n<li>square</li>\r\n<li>triangle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n```",
